    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Environmentalists vs. the Poor?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter from Eric Goldwasser says helping poor get richer will not save planet from global warming (Bjorn Lomborg Aug 26 Op-Ed)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Bjorn Lomborg is right that environmentalists who claim that we are running out of resources and polluting the planet are wrong (Op-Ed, Aug. 26). But I don't believe that by helping the poor get richer we can save the planet from global warming.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Bjorn Lomborg is right that environmentalists who claim that we are running out of resources and polluting the planet are wrong (Op-Ed, Aug. 26). But I don't believe that by helping the poor get richer we can save the planet from global warming.</p>
        <p>When the poor get rich enough to afford S.U.V.'s and McMansions, they will buy them just as we do. Does anyone believe that the planet can support 6 billion to 10 billion people living the American lifestyle that President Bush seems determined to preserve?</p>
        <p>ERIC GOLDWASSER  Yorktown Heights, N.Y., Aug. 26, 2002</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
